      <akn:section eId="sec_2_354_04">
        <akn:num>2-354.04</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Sole source procurements.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_2-354_04_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A contract may be awarded through noncompetitive negotiations when there is only one source for the required good or service.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_2-354_04_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The CPO shall make a determination and findings justifying the sole source procurement.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_2-354_04_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Notice of intent to enter into a sole source contract shall be posted on the Internet at least 10 days prior to award. The notice shall include:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_2-354_04_d">
      <akn:num>(d)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The contract shall be made available online within 7 days of the contract award.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
